Phase 3 partial: source rewrite + __edgeDynImport helper inject is in
place. Per-module importModuleDynamically callback bridging requires
mapping browser-V8 host parent URL → lib-V8 referrerSymbol via the
moduleRegistries WeakMap, which is keyed by edge's
host_defined_option_symbol private symbol. Implementing the bridge
needs either a C++ rebuild (set the symbol with a stable per-record
value at ModuleWrapCtor) or a side-channel registry. Tracked as a
Phase 5 followup. The rewrite itself is verified in the Phase 1/2/4
test suite; running the rewrite on dynamic-import-bearing source
produces a __edgeDynImport call that — when bound — will resolve via
the global callback (lib's importModuleDynamicallyCallback). Falls
back to native browser import() for absolute URLs (blob:, data:).
